1. Definition (0 se interview explain)

Abstract Factory ek creational design pattern hai jo related objects ke families create karta hai bina unki exact classes specify kiye.

Simple line:
👉 “Single object nahi… complete related objects ka group banega.”

🔹 2. Real Problem (kyun bana yeh pattern?)

Maan le tu UI bana raha hai:

Windows UI → Button, Checkbox
Mac UI → Button, Checkbox

Ab agar tu direct likhe:

new WindowsButton();
new MacCheckbox();

💥 mismatch ho gaya
UI toot jayega

👉 Solution:
✔ Ek hi family ke objects use karo

🔹 3. Concept samajh (core idea)

Factory bolti hai:
👉 “Shape chahiye? le lo”

Abstract Factory bolti hai:
👉 “Poora ecosystem chahiye? Windows ya Mac? main sab set dungi.”

🔹 4. Flow (step-by-step)
Step 1: Abstract products
interface Button {
    void paint();
}

interface Checkbox {
    void paint();
}
Step 2: Concrete products
class WindowsButton implements Button {
    public void paint() {
        System.out.println("Windows Button");
    }
}

class MacButton implements Button {
    public void paint() {
        System.out.println("Mac Button");
    }
}
Step 3: Abstract Factory
interface GUIFactory {
    Button createButton();
    Checkbox createCheckbox();
}
Step 4: Concrete Factories
class WindowsFactory implements GUIFactory {
    public Button createButton() {
        return new WindowsButton();
    }

    public Checkbox createCheckbox() {
        return new WindowsCheckbox();
    }
}

class MacFactory implements GUIFactory {
    public Button createButton() {
        return new MacButton();
    }

    public Checkbox createCheckbox() {
        return new MacCheckbox();
    }
}
Step 5: Client Code
GUIFactory factory = new WindowsFactory();

Button btn = factory.createButton();
Checkbox cb = factory.createCheckbox();

👉 Same family ke objects mile
👉 No mismatch

🔹 5. Rules (important for interview)
Multiple related objects (family) hone chahiye
Abstract factory define hoti hai
Concrete factories specific family create karti hain
Client ko actual class ka pata nahi hota
🔹 6. Features
Family-based object creation
Loose coupling
Consistency maintain karta hai
Scalable architecture
🔹 7. Advantages

✔ Compatible objects ensure karta hai
✔ Code clean aur modular hota hai
✔ Easily switch between families
✔ High-level abstraction

🔹 8. Disadvantages (real baat)

❌ Code ka size explode ho jata hai
❌ New product add karna painful ho jata hai
❌ Over-engineering in small projects

🔹 9. Real-world Use Cases
UI frameworks (Windows / Mac themes)
Cross-platform apps
Database drivers families
Spring (Bean families, configs)